From 46a4a9bd483cb6df503d64a963c348174b39d57e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Apr 2025 16:04:58 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] UPSTREAM:DP:ath12k: Add 4addr tx multicast packet support

In 4addr, AP wired backbone to STA wired backbone ping fails due to ARP
request not getting answered. Here 4addr ARP multicast packet is sent in
3addr, so that 4addr STA not honouring the 3addr ARP multicast packet.
Fix this issue by sending out multicast packet in 4addr format, firmware
expects peer meta flag instead of vdev meta flag in Tx descriptor.

Signed-off-by: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.h          |  2 ++
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c     |  3 ++
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.h     |  2 ++
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp.h    |  1 +
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c | 33 +++++++++++++++----
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.h |  2 +-
